Story 2 – Tasbih Counter & Progress Tracking
Story Statement

As a user, I want to track my current tasbih, total tasbih, and total recitations in separate cards, so that I can monitor my progress clearly.

UI / UX Specifications
Current Tasbih Count Card

Shape: Rounded rectangle (radius 15px).

Background: Light green tint (#E8F8F5).

Text:

Label: “Current Tasbih” – 14px, bold, dark green (#145A32).

Count: 28px, bold, dark green (#145A32).

Position: First card below Durood display card.

Size: Full width minus 30px margin.

Description: Shows tasbih count for the current cycle/session.

Total Tasbih Count Card

Background: Light blue tint (#EBF5FB).

Text:

Label: “Total Tasbih” – 14px, bold, dark blue (#1B4F72).

Count: 28px, bold, dark blue (#1B4F72).

Position: Left side of row (side-by-side).

Description: Shows the overall tasbih beads counted in total.

Total Recitation Count Card

Background: Light purple tint (#F5EBF9).

Text:

Label: “Total Recitations” – 14px, bold, dark purple (#4A235A).

Count: 28px, bold, dark purple (#4A235A).

Position: Right side of row (side-by-side with Total Tasbih card).

Description: Shows the total number of times the Durood has been completed.